[4] Ukraine
Date: Wed 16 May 2018 16:38 EEST
Source: RBC [in Russian, machine trans. edited]
https://www.rbc.ua/rus/news/kor-ukraine-nedelyu-zaboleli-1-4-tys-chelovek-1526477846.html


Over the past week more than 1400 people including 756 children contracted measles in Ukraine. This is reported on the website of the Ministry of Health.

"According to the operative data of the Public Health Center of the Ministry of Health of Ukraine, for the 19th week of 2018 [week of 7 May 2018], 1407 people became ill with measles: 651 adults and 756 children. The number of new cases in the last week increased, and the largest number of new cases were registered in Vinnitsa, Volyn, Kiev, Lviv, Lugansk, Rivne, Chernigov regions, as well as in the city of Kiev. The share of adults who have become ill with measles is also growing," the report says.

The Ministry of Health noted that since the beginning of the year [2018], 15 261 people have been ill with measles -- 6243 adults and 9018 children. During this time 8 people -- 6 children and 2 adults -- died from complications of the disease. Since the beginning of the year, most people have become ill with measles in Ivano-Frankivsk, Transcarpathia, Lviv, Odessa, and Chernivtsi regions.

Recall that the new 800 000 doses of measles, mumps, and rubella vaccine (MMR), which were previously delivered to Ukraine, have already been distributed among the oblasts. Most of the doses were distributed in such areas as Transcarpathia (72 508), Zaporozhye (52 208), Volyn (51 586).

