[5] New Zealand (South Island)
Date: Tue 15 May 2018 17:02 NZST
Source: Stuff [edited]
https://www.stuff.co.nz/national/health/103921855/fourteenth-measles-case-confirmed-in-south-island-outbreak


Measles has spread through the South Island after cases were found in Nelson, Christchurch, and Queenstown.

A person infected with measles visited a Christchurch mall, 2 supermarkets, and a pizza takeaway before realising they were sick.

They are the 15th case in the South Island related to a recent measles outbreak, including a baby and people in Nelson, Queenstown, and Wanaka. The 1st case was confirmed in early April [2018].

Medical officials have warned of the possibility of more cases and urged those with symptoms to call, rather than visit, their doctors.

