[6] Japan
Date: Tue 22 May 2018
Source: NHK World [edited]
https://www3.nhk.or.jp/nhkworld/en/news/20180522_32/


Health officials in Japan say as of [Mon 21 May 2018] more than 170 people across the country have been infected with measles. The outbreak began in the southwestern prefecture of Okinawa in March [2018].

The National Institute of Infectious Diseases said on [Tue 22 May 2018] that 99 people were infected in Okinawa, 23 in Aichi, central Japan, and 2 in Tokyo.

17 people have tested positive for the viral disease in Fukuoka, southwestern Japan.

The officials said the number of cases could increase due to the spring vacation period in late April and early May [2018], when large numbers of people travel around the country. ...

